		                	<h1 class="entry-title">WICS Winter Quarter Week 4: Jeopardy Night</h1>		                </div>
		                <footer class="entry-footer">
		                	<i class="fa fa-calendar-check-o" aria-hidden="true"></i> <span class="posted-on"><a href="https://wics.ics.uci.edu/wics-winter-quarter-week-4-jeopardy-night/" rel="bookmark"><time class="entry-date published" datetime="2019-02-14T00:14:59-07:00">02/14/2019</time><time class="updated" datetime="2019-02-19T00:20:27-07:00">02/19/2019</time></a></span><span class="author vcard"><i class="fa fa-user"></i><a class="url fn n" href="https://wics.ics.uci.edu/author/admin/">admin</a></span>
		                </footer><!-- .entry-footer -->

<p>On February 13 WICS members took a break from studying and got together to play a game of Jeopardy. Everyone got to have some delicious pizza before the game started. About 25 people attended and there were four teams of 4-5 people. Players had a lot of fun answering questions from categories such as WICS, UCI Culture, ICS Professors, Popular Culture, and Coding/Big O. When all the questions on the board were answered, the teams had to provide the answer to a riddle for the Final Jeopardy question. The teams decided on how much of their earnings from throughout the game they would bet on the question; if they got the question right they won that amount and if they didn’t, they would lose that amount. Each of the members of the winning team went home with a bag of free swag. Everyone who attended had a great time meeting and bonding with new and old friends!</p>
